post_cb({"20744647": {"ParentId": "20744526", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>This is standardized in 7.1.5/4 ([dcl.constexpr], \"The <code>constexpr</code> specifier\"):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_20744526_20744647_0\">The definition of a <em>constexpr</em> constructor shall satisfy the following constraints:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p id=\"so_20744526_20744647_1\">[...]</p></li>\n<li><p id=\"so_20744526_20744647_2\">every non-static data member and base class sub-object shall be initialized</p></li>\n<li><p id=\"so_20744526_20744647_3\">[...]</p></li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "596781", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "20744647", "Score": "9", "CreationDate": "2013-12-23T13:33:41.567", "LastActivityDate": "2013-12-23T13:33:41.567"}, "20744526": {"CommentCount": "3", "ViewCount": "213", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "1126943", "CreationDate": "2013-12-23T13:25:06.210", "LastActivityDate": "2013-12-23T13:33:41.567", "Title": "Isn't S a literal type?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "20744647", "LastEditDate": "2013-12-23T13:28:47.403", "Id": "20744526", "Score": "4", "Body": "<p>This code doesn't compile in <a href=\"http://coliru.stacked-crooked.com/a/b8f2bc93290c69c0\" rel=\"nofollow\">Coliru</a>, although it seems to comply with iso \u00a75.19 p2 9th bullet point and iso \u00a73.9 p10, i.e., <code>S</code> is a literal type and so, <code>S a(1);</code> should be considered a constant expression. In particular, iso \u00a73.9 p10 bullet point 3 doesn't say anything about unitialized members.</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\n\nstruct S\n{\n    int i;\n    float x;\n\n    constexpr S(int j) : i{j} {}\n};    \n\nint main()\n{\n    constexpr S a(1);\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><constexpr>", "OwnerUserId": "2548699", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_20744526_20744647_2": {"section_id": 5420, "quality": 1.0, "length": 8}, "so_20744526_20744647_0": {"section_id": 5420, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "length": 6}}, "n3337": {"so_20744526_20744647_2": {"section_id": 5215, "quality": 1.0, "length": 8}, "so_20744526_20744647_0": {"section_id": 5215, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "length": 6}}, "n4659": {"so_20744526_20744647_2": {"section_id": 6842, "quality": 1.0, "length": 8}, "so_20744526_20744647_0": {"section_id": 6842, "quality": 0.7142857142857143, "length": 5}}}});